Recipe Title: Veggie Stir-Fry Noodles

Description:
A quick and healthy stir-fry with colorful vegetables, tender noodles, and a savory sauce. Perfect for a weeknight meal!

Ingredients:

200g rice noodles or egg noodles

1 tbsp sesame oil

2 cloves garlic, minced

1 small onion, sliced

1 cup broccoli florets

1 cup bell peppers, sliced

1 carrot, julienned

2 tbsp soy sauce

1 tbsp oyster sauce (optional)

1 tsp chili sauce (optional for spice)

2 spring onions, chopped (for garnish)


Steps:

1. Cook noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
2. Heat sesame oil in a large pan or wok over medium-high heat.
3. Add garlic and onion, sauté until fragrant.
4. Add broccoli, bell peppers, and carrot. Stir-fry for 3–4 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
5. Add cooked noodles, soy sauce, oyster sauce, and chili sauce. Toss everything together until well combined.
6. Serve hot, garnished with chopped spring onions.



